Dry-Rubbed Crockpot Chicken

INGREDIENTS:
Dry Rub:
1 Tablespoon paprika
1 teaspoon dried thyme, crushed
1 teaspoon dried rubbed sage
1 Tablespoon brown sugar
1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper
1-1/2 teaspoons Kosher salt
1/2 teaspoon lemon pepper

3 chicken thighs
3 chicken drumsticks

PREPARATION:
Whisk together paprika, thyme, sage, brown sugar, cayenne pepper, salt, and
lemon pepper. 

Sprinkle dry rub evenly over both sides of the chicken thighs and legs.

Place chicken in a standard heavy skillet over medium heat and brown on both
sides.

Place chicken in crockpot. Cover with the lid and set to High.
Cook for 2 hours. (May cook on the Low setting for 3-1/2 to 4 hours.) 

Yield: 3 to 4 servings 
